Package Management
•	Install the package vim.
•	Check the version installed.
•	Remove the package ftp if it exists.

Solution:- 
RHEL/CentOS/Fedora -1-> dnf/yum install vim -y
                    2-> Check version 
                        vim --version
                    3-> dnf/yum remove ftp -y
    Ubuntu/Debian - 1-> apt updatae
                        apt install vim -y
                    2-> check version
                        vim --version
                    3-> apt remove ftp -y
